    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase funding for mental health crisis patient aftercare",
        "additional_details": "Mind found that 1 in 10 people don't get follow ups.\r\nIn a survey, they found that those who weren\u2019t followed up appropriately were twice as likely to attempt suicide. \r\n \r\nAround 110,000 people end up in hospital with a mental health crisis each year.\r\nSupport needs to be available right away, not just promised with no guarantee of when the help will be provided. Too many people aren't getting this.\r\nNo-one should be left feeling alone after been discharged from hospital with mental health, this can result in suicide which is devastating for everyone involved.\r\n \r\nhttps://www.mind.org.uk/news-campaigns/news/thousands-left-to-cope-alone-after-leaving-mental-health-hospital-putting-their-lives-at-risk/ ",
        "background": "More aftercare support including regular follow up phone calls, free texts of helplines available and reassurance of an appointment.",
